1 SECTION 6. G.S. 90-414.4(a1)(1) reads as rewritten:
2 "(1) The following providers of Medicaid services licensed to operate in the State
3 that have an electronic health record system shall begin submitting, at a
4 minimum, demographic and clinical data by June 1, 2018:
5 a. Hospitals as defined in G.S. 131E-176(13).Hospitals, defined for the
6 purposes of this section as public or private institutions which are
7 primarily engaged in providing to inpatients, by or under supervision
8 of physicians, diagnostic services and therapeutic services for medical
9 diagnosis, treatment, and care of injured, disabled, or sick persons, or
10 rehabilitation services for the rehabilitation of injured, disabled, or
11 sick persons. The term includes all facilities licensed pursuant to
12 G.S. 131E-77, except long-term care hospitals.
13 b. Physicians licensed to practice under Article 1 of Chapter 90 of the
14 General Statutes, except for licensed physicians whose primary area
15 of practice is psychiatry.
16 c. Physician assistants as defined in 21 NCAC 32S.0201.21 NCAC 32S
17 .0201.
18 d. Nurse practitioners as defined in 21 NCAC 36.0801.21 NCAC 36
19 .0801."
20 SECTION 7. G.S. 90-414.4(b)(1) reads as rewritten:
21 "(1) Each hospital, as defined in G.S. 131E-176(13) that has an electronic health
22 record system.hospital."
23 SECTION 8. G.S. 113A-12(3)e. reads as rewritten:
24 "e. A health care facility financed pursuant to Article 1 of Chapter 131A
25 of the General Statutes or receiving a certificate of need under Article
26 9 of Chapter 131E of the General Statutes."
27 SECTION 9. G.S. 122C-23.1(e) reads as rewritten:
28 "(e) As used in this section, "residential treatment facility" means a "residential facility"
29 as defined in and licensed under this Chapter, but not subject to Certificate of Need requirements
30 under Article 9 of Chapter 131E of the General Statutes.Chapter."
31 SECTION 10. G.S. 131D-2.4(a) reads as rewritten:
32 "(a) Licensure. – Except for those facilities exempt under G.S. 131D-2.3, the Department
33 of Health and Human Services shall inspect and license all adult care homes. The Department
34 shall issue a license for a facility not currently licensed as an adult care home for a period of six
35 months. If the licensee demonstrates substantial compliance with Articles 1 and 3 of this Chapter
36 and rules adopted thereunder, the Department shall issue a license for the balance of the calendar
37 year. A facility not currently licensed as an adult care home that was licensed as an adult care
38 home within the preceding 12 months is considered an existing health service facility for the
39 purposes of G.S. 131E-184(a)(8)."
40 SECTION 11. G.S. 131E-13(a)(1) reads as rewritten:
41 "(1) The corporation shall continue to provide the same or similar clinical hospital
42 services to its patients in medical-surgery, obstetrics, pediatrics, outpatient
43 and emergency treatment, including emergency services for the indigent, that
44 the hospital facility provided prior to the lease, sale, or conveyance. These
45 services may be terminated only as prescribed by Certificate of Need Law
46 prescribed in Article 9 of Chapter 131E of the General Statutes, or, if
47 Certificate of Need Law is inapplicable, by review procedure designed to
48 guarantee public participation pursuant to rules adopted by the Secretary of
49 the Department of Health and Human Services."
50 SECTION 12. G.S. 131E-84(a1) reads as rewritten:
House Bill 455-First Edition Page 3

General Assembly Of North Carolina Session 2025
1 "(a1) In the event of a declaration of a state of emergency by the Governor in accordance
2 with Article 1A of Chapter 166A of the General Statutes, a declaration of a national emergency
3 by the President of the United States, a declaration of a public health emergency by the Secretary
4 of the United States Department of Health and Human Services; or to the extent necessary to
5 allow for consistency with any temporary waiver or modification issued by the Secretary of the
6 United States Department of Health and Human Services or the Centers for Medicare and
7 Medicaid Services under section 1135 or 1812(f) of the Social Security Act; or when the Division
8 of Health Service Regulation determines the existence of an emergency that poses a risk to the
9 health or safety of patients, the Division of Health Service Regulation may do either or both of
10 the following:
11 (1) Temporarily temporarily waive any rules of the Commission pertaining to
12 hospitals.
13 (2) Notwithstanding G.S. 131E-183, allow a hospital to temporarily increase its
14 bed capacity."
15 SECTION 13. G.S. 131E-136(4) reads as rewritten:
16 "(4) "Home health agency" means a home care agency which is certified to receive
17 Medicare and Medicaid reimbursement for providing nursing care, therapy,
18 medical social services, and home health aide services on a part-time,
19 intermittent basis as set out in G.S. 131E-176(12), and is thereby also subject
20 to Article 9 of Chapter 131E.basis."
21 SECTION 14. The following laws are repealed:
22 (1) Article 9 of Chapter 131E of the General Statutes.
23 (2) G.S. 130A-45.02(i).
24 (3) G.S. 131E-78.3(c).
25 (4) G.S. 131E-146(3), as enacted by Section 3.2(b) of S.L. 2023-7.
26 (5) G.S. 131E-147.5, as enacted by Section 3.2(c) of S.L. 2023-7.
27 (6) G.S. 143B-1292.
28 (7) G.S. 150B-2(8a)k.
29 (8) G.S. 150B-21.1(a)(6).
30 SECTION 15. This act becomes effective January 1, 2026.
